*** 2018-06-04 Monday
[2018-06-04 Mon]
Today we learned the details of how this course will operate, the
expectations between the students and professor, and a recap on
rhetoric. It was nice to meet all of our classmates in a smaller
classroom setting.

Rhetoric
- "Rhetoric is the ability in each particular case to discover the
  available means of persuasion."
- "Rhetoric is a mode of altering reality, not by the direct
  application of energy to objects, but by the creation of discourse
  which changes reality through the mediation of thought and action."
- "The use of words by human agents to form attitudes or induce
  actions in other human agents."
- "The use of language as a symbolic means of inducing cooperation in
  beings that by nature respond to symbols."

Freewrite:
"What about this class excites you most?"
- It was very pleasing to hear that grades will be argued for. This is
  something that sounds very confortable to me. Having a smaller class
  size is also interesting, as it seems it may allow for more involved
  discussions or arguments.

"What about this class scares you most?"
- English courses in general tend to scare me a tad, in that the
  learning outcomes for some previously taken did not seem to
  explicitly stated -- unecessary ambiguity.

Why do we make arguments? I like this idea of argumentation, as a
non-negative activity.
- Ethos
- Pathos
- Logos
- Kairos
- Deliberative (Future)
- Epideictic (Present)
- Forensic (Past)
