**** DONE A.2 Learning Record
- reflect on your development as it relates to the course strand

Thinking about my own capabilities as a reader and writer, it would
seem that I generally have a very difficult time communicating my
thoughts accurately and entirely. To second my girlfriend, I do feel
as though I tend to spend a great deal of time thinking very deeply
about questions. My guess would be that this causes the opinions that
I gather to be riddled with details and nuances that take me a long
time to generalize, or compress into more concise forms, should I be
be asked to express myself.

This being said, I also feel that when I am able to set aside enough
time to collect all of my thoughts on some question, my arguments are
generally quite good, per feedback from others. 

Of course, considering that this response is indeed a situation in
which I must respond to a very broad question, there are many more
experiences that I've had and could delve into as they relate to my
abilites in argumentation and communication. If anything, this is
perhaps to say that I want to communicate the best judgements of
things as possible in all my arguments, acknowledging my own perpetual
fallibility as a human. Since it is always the case that there exists
more to learn and that my thoughts will differ in some way from the
truth, claiming any real knowledge of any one thing for me is
impossble. It follows that any form of criticism of my opinions is a
good thing - an opportunity to rethink my argument - and it is this
kind of socratic and enlightenment style of thinking that I think has
put me in a good position to analyze and commmunicate sound and
informative arguments; but we'll see...

