**** OOPS Read EAA chs. 16 & 17
**** Project 1, Stakeholder Analysis
- Every team will generate a list of major stakeholders within the
  controversy that your group is studying
- Within your team, each group member will select one stakeholder that
  they will become an expert on, irrespective of your own position on
  the issue
- Each person will:
    - Write a 6-page (1800 words) rhetorical analysis of one
      stakeholder's position, argument, and rhetorical strategies
    - Cite at least one source made by the stakeholder
    - These analyses should strive to provide a fair analysis of your
      stakeholder's position by quoting from and closely engage with
      source /produced/ by those stakeholders.
***** Focus/Purpose/genre
Makes an argument about the stakeholder's use of rhetoric (not about
the issue itself). Clearly identifies a stakeholder and offers
effective analysis of the stakeholder's position and arguments.
