**** DONE EAA Ch. 14 & 15 and "Document Design"
CLOSED: [2018-06-19 Tue 10:37]
***** Document Design
- *Document Design* = visual appearance (not content)
- *Unity* = repetition and consistency. 
  "Do all elements in my document work together visually?"
- *Variety* = varied, topic specific design choices
- *Balance* = harmony/equilibrum/proportionality
- *Emphasis* = drawing attention to important parts
- *Layout* = spatial arrangement
- *White Space* = easier to read
- ACADEMIC vs. BUSINESS WRITING ?
- *Typeface* = a general font (Verdana, Courier)
- *Font* = a specific font (Century *bold*, Verdana /italics/, etc.)
- *Visuals*
    - make simple and uncluttered
    - only when necessary
    - label/number tables and figures
    - balance b/w figs and text
    - give credit if not your own
***** EAA 14
***** EAA 15
- Formal Presentations: *Purpose*, *Audience*, *Structure*
- Strong introductions and conclusions
- Clear structures and signposts
- Straightforward syntax and concrete diction
- Repetition, parallelism, and climactic order
- *Oral* presentations: practice, time, and record
- Websites, Blogs, Wikis, Videos
